		<div class="comment_text"><p>I'm not sure how we lived without our's either.  Some of my favorite features (TiVo):</p><p>1.  Pause live tv<br>2.  Remote scheduling (from the web)<br>3.  Streaming music from my other computers to the TiVo<br>4.  Streaming Pictures from my other computers<br>5.  The JavaHMO project<br>6.  TiVo's wishlist capabilities.  We use this for all sorts of things such as favorite actors and directors.  Also use it for cooking - put in an ingredient or food and it records related shows.  And for travel.  We put in "Malta" before our Malta trip and it recorded several related shows.<br>7.  I like that TiVo uses my ratings and viewing history to make suggestions.  It's done a decent job suggesting some art-house and foreign films that have turned out to be big winners.<br>8.  Commercial skip.  I just love this one.<br>9.  The TiVo remote.  This is one of the best designed remotes I've used.<br>10.  If you have more than one TiVo, you can send a show from the TiVo in one room to the TiVo in the other.</p></div>
