		<div class="comment_text"><p>I too have the Motorolla DVR box from Comcast.  The only reason I got it was to record HDTV content.  I have had a Tivo for years, where have you been?  :-)  I will day that recording HD directly from the box works great!</p><p>The lack of funcitonality on the DVR compared to Tivo is very disappointing.  For instance, there doesn't seem to be a way to record a "season pass" like Tivo (all new episodes of a series) or even basic VCR functionality like record this channel every week at this time.  Without this, it is almost useless.</p><p>Now that Tivo is only $99 (plus service) if you like the crude DVR in the cable box, you should really try a full Tivo for a month.  Especially if you aren't in to HDTV yet, you will *not* be disappointed.  I bought one when they were $400 (plus $200 for lifetime service) and after the first few days, my wife loved it more than I did. :-)</p><p>The problem (if you will) with the cable DVR is that *any* DVR funcitonality is awesome.  It much easier to get it in the Cable box, and cheaper.  People like yourselves will love it.  They wont 'need' Tivo, wont buy it.  Since Tivo hasn't been able to work a deal with any cable company, they wont grow and may die.  And that would be a *very* bad thing.</p></div>
